    <h2>The Service</h2>
    <p>HelloDeploy (&ldquo;the platform&rdquo;) is a free, self-hosted web application deployment service operated by Henson Sagorsor as part of an MIT capstone project. It lets registered users deploy web applications from GitHub repositories to a shared server environment.</p>

    <h2>Acceptance</h2>
    <p>By creating an account or using HelloDeploy you agree to these Terms of Service, the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>, <a href="/cookies">Cookie Policy</a>, <a href="/acceptable-use">Acceptable Use Policy</a>, <a href="/service-limits">Service Limits</a>, <a href="/data-processing">Data Processing Terms</a>, <a href="/copyright">Copyright Policy</a>, and <a href="/security">Security Policy</a>. If you do not agree, do not use the service.</p>

    <h2>Eligibility</h2>
    <p>You must be at least 13 years old to create an account. By registering you confirm this. The platform is currently invitation-only during the pilot phase; account creation requires approval from the platform administrator.</p>

    <h2>Your Account</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You are responsible for keeping your credentials secure. Do not share your password.</li>
      <li>You are responsible for all activity that occurs under your account.</li>
      <li>Notify the administrator immediately if you suspect unauthorised access.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Beta and Pilot Status</h2>
    <p>HelloDeploy is currently a limited pilot and capstone project. Features, limits, supported runtimes, routing behavior, and availability may change. Do not use HelloDeploy for safety-critical, regulated, or production workloads that require a formal service-level agreement.</p>

    <h2>What You Deploy</h2>
    <p>You retain ownership of all source code and content you deploy. By connecting a GitHub repository you grant HelloDeploy the access necessary to clone and build that repository on your behalf. This access is limited to repositories you explicitly authorise through the GitHub App installation.</p>
    <p>You must comply with the <a href="/acceptable-use">Acceptable Use Policy</a>. Prohibited deployments include (but are not limited to) malware, phishing sites, illegal content, and cryptocurrency miners.</p>

    <h2>Service Limits</h2>
    <p>The platform enforces resource quotas described on the <a href="/service-limits">Service Limits</a> page. The administrator may adjust your quota at their discretion.</p>

    <h2>User Applications and End Users</h2>
    <p>You are responsible for your deployed application, its content, its users, and any personal data your application collects or processes. HelloDeploy provides deployment infrastructure only. You must provide your own privacy notices, terms, licenses, consent flows, and compliance controls for your application where required.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>HelloDeploy depends on services such as GitHub, MongoDB Atlas, Resend, Cloudflare, Docker, and other infrastructure providers. Your use of HelloDeploy may also be subject to those providers&rsquo; terms and policies.</p>

